  "riddle": "1. In the heart of Sangamon County, seek the township that first drew breath in what year? This is your starting point.\n\n2. Ascend to the heights of this township — how far above sea level does it stand?\n\n3. Count the number of spiritual havens that grace the area surrounding this township. How many are there?\n\n4. Now, take the elevation discovered in clue 2 and blend it with the count of churches from clue 3. What is their combined total?\n\n5. Turning to a prominent figure from Illinois, calculate how many days stood between the dawn of 1875 and the Ides of March in 2026.\n\n6. Among the numbers you found in clue 5, what is the next prime that follows? Discover this hidden gem.\n\n7. Finally, take the year from clue 1 and subtract the count of churches from clue 3. Then, find the absolute value and compute its remainder when divided by 10. This will yield your final single-digit answer.",
